{
  "stem": "16473.2",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 286.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "At one point, there was talk about what should be done with me because my parents realized that the Nazis were coming close.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I was in on this.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I knew that they were talking about sending me to Switzerland.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I'd say, I don't want to go to Switzerland, I don't want to leave you.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And I'd carry on tremendously.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And as it turned out, for some reason that didn't pan out.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And ever since then, my dad's thing, when I worry about something, he'd say, [SOBBING] it's Switzerland, it's Switzerland, like don't worry about it.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "It will never happen.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] I guess I'm just trying to say that, for the most part, we didn't look reality in-- at least the children were not made to look at reality or to understand it, but we understood it, it instinctively and just by the feeling tone of our parents, I-- I think.",
      "word_count": 55
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Despite the fact that I knew that this was happening, I also knew that my mother spoke German with-- it was an SS troop that was occupying the place.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "My mother was friendly with and spoke German with the captain.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I know that I was given-- through my mother, I was given gifts that were taken from other children.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So I had silver spoons and things with another child's name on it.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And it was strange because [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] I don't know if it was my mother's [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] sense of humanity or what it was, but when the SS troop had to retreat and this captain had to retreat, he was very sick and they were in a bad shape.",
      "word_count": 53
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And my mother was sorry for him.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
